# CODEOWNERS — Human-in-the-loop enforcement
#
# These paths require explicit review/approval before merge.
# Protects infrastructure scripts, design system, templates, and policy docs
# from unreviewed changes.

# ── Templates & design system ─────────────────────────────
# Changes affect every rendered page.
templates/                @tak-goto
templates/components/     @tak-goto
design-system/            @tak-goto

# ── Build infrastructure ──────────────────────────────────
# build.js: controls how all pages are generated (CSS fingerprint,
#   OGP, sitemap, robots, public/ copy). A single bad line breaks
#   every page.
# scripts/: lint.js gates all CI runs. Weakening checks here
#   silently degrades quality assurance.
build.js                  @tak-goto
scripts/                  @tak-goto

# ── CI / CD workflows ─────────────────────────────────────
# Workflow changes carry privilege-escalation risk.
# Dependabot PRs targeting these files will also require review,
# which is intentional — action version bumps should be human-verified.
.github/workflows/        @tak-goto
.github/CODEOWNERS        @tak-goto

# ── Policy & governance documents ────────────────────────
# GOVERNANCE.md and CLAUDE.md define the operating rules for this repo.
# Weakening them without review defeats the governance model.
GOVERNANCE.md             @tak-goto
CLAUDE.md                 @tak-goto
